    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Subgoal Tracking Solves"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A goal decomposed into subgoals creates a tree of obligations. Without explicit tracking, the agent must re-derive what has been done and what remains on every planning cycle. Subgoal tracking maintains a persistent tree where each node carries a status, a result, and a parent reference \u2014 making progress queryable at any level of the hierarchy without re-reading execution history."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Subgoal Tree with Status Tracking",
          "title": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Track at the leaf level, roll up to the root. A parent node is DONE only when all its children are DONE \u2014 this invariant is maintained automatically by the tree, not by the planner."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The GoalNode Dataclass"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each node in the tracking tree holds its own status and enough context for the planner to resume work on that node independently. Children are stored by reference so roll-up can traverse the tree bottom-up."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from __future__ import annotations\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional, Any\n\nclass GoalStatus(Enum):\n    PENDING     = \"pending\"\n    IN_PROGRESS = \"in_progress\"\n    DONE        = \"done\"\n    FAILED      = \"failed\"\n    SKIPPED     = \"skipped\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass GoalNode:\n    id: str\n    objective: str\n    success_criteria: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    parent: Optional[GoalNode] = field(default=None, repr=False)\n    children: list[GoalNode] = field(default_factory=list)\n    status: GoalStatus = GoalStatus.PENDING\n    result: Optional[Any] = None\n\n    # --- tree helpers ---\n    def is_leaf(self) -> bool:\n        return len(self.children) == 0\n\n    def leaves(self) -> list[GoalNode]:\n        if self.is_leaf():\n            return [self]\n        result = []\n        for child in self.children:\n            result.extend(child.leaves())\n        return result\n\n    def next_pending(self) -> Optional[GoalNode]:\n        \"\"\"DFS: first leaf that is PENDING and whose parent is IN_PROGRESS or root.\"\"\"\n        if self.is_leaf() and self.status == GoalStatus.PENDING:\n            return self\n        for child in self.children:\n            found = child.next_pending()\n            if found:\n                return found\n        return None\n\n    def rollup_status(self) -> GoalStatus:\n        \"\"\"Derive parent status from children \u2014 do not set manually.\"\"\"\n        if not self.children:\n            return self.status\n        child_statuses = {c.rollup_status() for c in self.children}\n        if child_statuses == {GoalStatus.DONE}:\n            return GoalStatus.DONE\n        if GoalStatus.FAILED in child_statuses:\n            return GoalStatus.FAILED\n        if GoalStatus.IN_PROGRESS in child_statuses:\n            return GoalStatus.IN_PROGRESS\n        return GoalStatus.PENDING\n\n    def progress(self) -> tuple[int, int]:\n        \"\"\"Returns (done_leaves, total_leaves).\"\"\"\n        all_leaves = self.leaves()\n        done = sum(1 for l in all_leaves if l.status == GoalStatus.DONE)\n        return done, len(all_leaves)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building the Goal Tree"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The LLM decomposes the root goal into child GoalNodes. Each child can be further decomposed if it is still composite. The decomposition stops at primitive goals \u2014 tasks small enough for a single tool call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, json, re\n\nDECOMPOSE_PROMPT = \"\"\"Decompose the following goal into {n} parallel sub-goals.\n\nParent goal: {objective}\nSuccess criteria: {criteria}\n\nEach sub-goal must:\n- Be independently achievable (no dependency between siblings)\n- Be concrete enough to execute with a single tool call, or further decomposable\n- Together cover the full parent objective\n\nReturn JSON array:\n[{{\"id\": str, \"objective\": str, \"success_criteria\": [str], \"is_leaf\": bool}}]\n\"\"\"\n\ndef decompose_node(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    node: GoalNode,\n    n: int = 3,\n) -> list[GoalNode]:\n    prompt = DECOMPOSE_PROMPT.format(\n        objective=node.objective,\n        criteria=\"\\n\".join(f\"  - {c}\" for c in node.success_criteria),\n        n=n,\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=768,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    raw = resp.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\[.*\\]\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return []\n    data = json.loads(m.group())\n    children = [\n        GoalNode(\n            id=sg[\"id\"],\n            objective=sg[\"objective\"],\n            success_criteria=sg.get(\"success_criteria\", []),\n            parent=node,\n        )\n        for sg in data\n    ]\n    node.children = children\n    return children\n\n\ndef build_goal_tree(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    root: GoalNode,\n    max_depth: int = 3,\n    branching: int = 3,\n    depth: int = 0,\n) -> GoalNode:\n    if depth >= max_depth:\n        return root\n    children = decompose_node(client, root, branching)\n    for child in children:\n        # Only recurse if the child objective is still composite\n        if len(child.objective.split()) > 8:  # heuristic: long obj = composite\n            build_goal_tree(client, child, max_depth, branching, depth + 1)\n    return root\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executing and Updating the Tree"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The executor picks the next pending leaf, executes it, then updates its status. Roll-up propagates completion upward automatically \u2014 the executor never sets a parent node's status directly."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def complete_leaf(node: GoalNode, result: Any) -> None:\n    node.result = result\n    node.status = GoalStatus.DONE\n    # Propagate upward\n    parent = node.parent\n    while parent is not None:\n        rolled = parent.rollup_status()\n        if parent.status != rolled:\n            parent.status = rolled\n        parent = parent.parent\n\n\ndef fail_leaf(node: GoalNode, error: str) -> None:\n    node.result = {\"error\": error}\n    node.status = GoalStatus.FAILED\n    parent = node.parent\n    while parent is not None:\n        parent.status = parent.rollup_status()\n        parent = parent.parent\n\n\ndef run_goal_tree(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    root: GoalNode,\n    execute_fn,\n    max_steps: int = 50,\n) -> GoalNode:\n    root.status = GoalStatus.IN_PROGRESS\n    for _ in range(max_steps):\n        leaf = root.next_pending()\n        if leaf is None:\n            break   # all leaves done or failed\n        leaf.status = GoalStatus.IN_PROGRESS\n        try:\n            result = execute_fn(leaf)\n            complete_leaf(leaf, result)\n        except Exception as e:\n            fail_leaf(leaf, str(e))\n    return root\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Querying Progress"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The tracker can answer planning-relevant questions at any point in execution: what percentage of leaves are done, which subtrees have failures, and which nodes are ready to start (all dependents satisfied)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def progress_report(root: GoalNode) -> str:\n    done, total = root.progress()\n    pct = int(100 * done / total) if total else 0\n    lines = [f\"Overall: {done}/{total} leaves done ({pct}%)\", \"\"]\n\n    def _render(node: GoalNode, indent: int) -> None:\n        icon = {\"pending\":\"\u25ef\",\"in_progress\":\"\u27f3\",\"done\":\"\u2713\",\"failed\":\"\u2717\",\"skipped\":\"\u2014\"}\n        lines.append(\n            \" \" * indent\n            + icon.get(node.status.value, \"?\")\n            + \" \"\n            + node.objective[:60]\n        )\n        for child in node.children:\n            _render(child, indent + 2)\n\n    _render(root, 0)\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef failed_subtrees(root: GoalNode) -> list[GoalNode]:\n    result = []\n    def _collect(node: GoalNode) -> None:\n        if node.status == GoalStatus.FAILED:\n            result.append(node)\n            return  # don't descend into already-failed subtrees\n        for child in node.children:\n            _collect(child)\n    _collect(root)\n    return result\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Verification: Goal Completion Check"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the tree reaches DONE status, a verification step confirms the root goal's success criteria are all satisfied. This is a separate LLM call that summarises leaf results and evaluates each criterion."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "VERIFY_PROMPT = \"\"\"Verify whether a goal has been achieved.\n\nGoal: {objective}\nSuccess criteria:\n{criteria}\n\nEvidence from completed sub-goals:\n{evidence}\n\nFor each criterion, state whether it is met and cite the relevant evidence.\nRespond with JSON:\n{{\"criteria_met\": {{\"criterion text\": bool}}, \"overall_success\": bool, \"notes\": str}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef verify_goal_completion(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    root: GoalNode,\n) -> dict:\n    evidence = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  - {leaf.objective}: {str(leaf.result)[:200]}\"\n        for leaf in root.leaves()\n        if leaf.status == GoalStatus.DONE\n    )\n    criteria_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  - {c}\" for c in root.success_criteria\n    )\n    prompt = VERIFY_PROMPT.format(\n        objective=root.objective,\n        criteria=criteria_text,\n        evidence=evidence,\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    raw = resp.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\{.*\\}\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    return json.loads(m.group()) if m else {\"overall_success\": False}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
